Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.30,0:00:06.49,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I am Ms. Frieren's student.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.98,0:00:10.41,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,You pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.37,0:00:13.34,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.08,0:00:27.00,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,You're there like the wind
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.00,0:00:31.63,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Closing your eyes at sunset
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.63,0:00:37.26,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what's on your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.55,0:00:42.60,Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(857,1)\blur0.25\fs35\fnGeorgia\fsp3.9\c&HFFFE65&\pos(328,254)\clip(109,253,547,294)\t(3943,4986,\clip(109,253,110,294))}Beyond Journey's End
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.97,0:00:45.98,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,With your eyelids open
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.98,0:00:50.57,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Your eyes shone like glass
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.57,0:00:57.32,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,It faintly smelled like a sunny day
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.25,0:01:08.46,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Clear up the sky, let flowers bloom
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.46,0:01:12.67,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Bloom and blame it on the sunny sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.67,0:01:17.05,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even the rain, when it stops
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.05,0:01:22.06,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Will make you shine in the sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.06,0:01:27.44,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Calm the stirring sounds in my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.44,0:01:31.48,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,We go like the sunny wind
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.48,0:01:35.90,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Go on and fly over that cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.90,0:01:40.74,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Further and further away
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.86,0:01:50.87,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Denken the Imperial Mage. \NI know all about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.78,0:01:53.91,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm honored.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.67,0:02:02.05,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,A self-made military mage who rose to be \Nthe most influential in the northern lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.63,0:02:04.62,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,It's an oft-heard heroic tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.89,0:02:10.27,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I wish I could've met you \Nwhen you were still young,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.07,0:02:16.85,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,full of drive and ambition.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.88,0:02:22.70,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I have no interest in burnt-out ashes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.34,0:02:27.64,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Or so I believed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.08,0:02:33.00,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you feel differently now?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.59,0:02:38.76,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,When you saw me, you thought about \Nhow you'd fight me, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.10,0:02:45.14,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Only for a moment. \NI immediately abandoned the idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.49,0:02:49.85,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,You pass. There's still a fire in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.77,0:02:53.77,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Normally it wouldn't even occur \Nto someone to fight me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.11,0:02:56.10,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.59,0:03:02.99,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,You pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.99,0:03:06.59,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,What? But we haven't even spoken yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.06,0:03:09.05,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Do we need to?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.63,0:03:12.77,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,I guess not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.77,0:03:13.69,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.74,0:03:20.05,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Is this some kind of joke?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.05,0:03:20.97,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.45,0:03:23.86,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,This is the first-class mage exam.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.86,0:03:27.36,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of idiot never even sets foot \Ninto the examination grounds?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.77,0:03:34.26,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see, my flesh-and-blood \Nbody is here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.26,0:03:35.91,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't want to be disqualified.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.91,0:03:41.04,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Throughout the exam period, your actual \Nbody never left your hometown.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.08,0:03:44.30,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Are you enjoying some tea right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.41,0:03:49.92,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.27,0:03:52.25,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,Not even Übel noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.20,0:03:56.22,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,You've got guts. You pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.57,0:03:57.72,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.58,0:04:03.08,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,You're Wirbel, captain of \Nthe Northern Magic Corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.08,0:04:07.71,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Of the second-class mages I know, \Nyou're the most combat-oriented.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.73,0:04:12.78,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,With a single look, you realized \Nyou couldn't beat me in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.29,0:04:15.99,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,But that wasn't a judgment made out of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.50,0:04:21.35,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,An idiot prone to picking fights he can't win\Nwouldn't even make it to second-class mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.99,0:04:23.45,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.19,0:04:26.99,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, what's your favorite spell?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.90,0:04:30.49,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Magic is a tool for killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.49,0:04:32.49,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,I neither like nor dislike any spells.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.38,0:04:35.86,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,You pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.86,0:04:36.91,Default,SEIRE,0000,0000,0000,,Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.38,0:04:44.56,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,What did you think when you saw me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.89,0:04:50.51,Default,METHODE,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I thought you were small and cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.84,0:04:56.03,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with this year's test-takers?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.89,0:04:58.11,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,You pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.86,0:05:06.04,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.89,0:05:11.54,Default,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies. We do have \Na bumper crop this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.28,0:05:16.71,Default,SCHARF,0000,0000,0000,,I failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.71,0:05:18.04,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,There's always next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.38,0:05:20.55,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,Stop following me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.32,0:05:23.13,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Three years, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.42,0:05:26.81,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, I passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.81,0:05:30.11,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.63,0:05:32.81,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.39,0:05:37.74,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I made it this far because of you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.78,0:05:42.05,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, I can visit a certain grave \Nin my hometown.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.84,0:05:44.74,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.60,0:05:54.45,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Fern.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.45,0:05:56.00,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Have you decided yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.13,0:06:08.54,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.37,0:06:08.54,DefaultOverlap,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,Old man, I want these.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.99,0:06:14.13,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.84,0:06:21.45,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be shy. Eat up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.45,0:06:26.38,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,When I was young, I hardly \Never got to eat sweet things.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.06,0:06:28.73,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.20,0:06:36.08,DefaultItalics,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.32,0:06:41.29,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Have some, young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.40,0:06:45.10,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.22,0:06:54.23,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.82,0:06:57.56,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Denken the Imperial Mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.87,0:07:00.83,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,An imperial mage?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.44,0:07:07.52,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,You mean he's a noble?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.52,0:07:11.62,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for speaking so casually to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.62,0:07:16.37,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine. I came to this city \Nas a mage like any other.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.37,0:07:20.95,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,But you shouldn't feel obliged \Nto treat a stranger like me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.95,0:07:23.75,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I have no other use for my money.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.75,0:07:26.45,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,There must be something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.45,0:07:28.50,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,He's right. Don't you have grandchildren?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.65,0:07:33.76,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I have no children or grandchildren.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.76,0:07:37.51,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,My wife passed away when \NI was in my mid-twenties.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.40,0:07:42.15,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,She was always sickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.12,0:07:44.98,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,She was the daughter of a frontier noble
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.98,0:07:48.36,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,of the Northern Plateau who was \Ndefeated in a political dispute.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.16,0:07:54.20,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Back then, I was in need of both \Nwealth and influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.20,0:07:57.81,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Those were the only ways I knew to save her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.49,0:08:02.00,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,When Serie established the \NContinental Magic Association
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.00,0:08:04.55,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,and began offering the privilege,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.55,0:08:07.83,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,it was just after my wife had already passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.72,0:08:11.67,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I'd never felt more powerless.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.95,0:08:20.94,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,It's ironic. These days, I could \Norder entire nations around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.05,0:08:23.15,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Fern.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.69,0:08:28.57,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,For me, magic was only ever a tool \Nto resolve political disputes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.51,0:08:37.34,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Tell Frieren she reminded me \Nof how fun magic can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.18,0:08:42.00,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,The whole reason I became a mage was because
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.00,0:08:44.21,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I admired her deeds in the party of heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.10,0:08:49.25,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You should tell her that yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.25,0:08:51.70,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure she'd be glad to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.50,0:08:56.64,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. That's what I'll do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.32,0:09:09.60,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The magical city of Äußerst didn't disappoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.60,0:09:11.79,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I bought a bunch of good grimoires.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.18,0:09:20.53,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, old woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.91,0:09:24.09,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,You want those in this basket, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.76,0:09:30.08,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,How could you just ignore her?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.08,0:09:32.76,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I did think about it a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.76,0:09:34.26,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Just a little?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.08,0:09:39.42,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised. I thought one of Himmel's \Nparty members would be...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.42,0:09:41.77,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Would be what?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.20,0:09:46.76,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,If anything, you surprised me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.46,0:09:51.02,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You tried to kill Fern's party \Nduring the first test, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.02,0:09:53.08,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Fern complained to me about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.08,0:09:55.85,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,She said you seemed like someone \Nwho'd kick a dog out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.63,0:09:58.24,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,I get that a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.06,0:10:00.99,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,All I did was threaten them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.11,0:10:06.92,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Though there was one of them whose death \Nwould probably make the world a better place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.11,0:10:12.99,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,I'd do anything to protect my hometown.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.11,0:10:20.05,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to become a first-class mage for \Nthe privilege of learning any spell I desired.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.05,0:10:25.01,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,With a more powerful spell, \NI can slaughter more demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.46,0:10:33.29,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,But even in other parts of the world, \NI do everything I can to help people in need.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.77,0:10:34.77,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.95,0:10:40.74,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,My hometown is on the northern frontier.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.78,0:10:45.27,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,There are countless stories \Nabout Himmel the Hero there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.14,0:10:50.56,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,The conquest of the Thousand-Mirror Tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.56,0:10:53.25,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,His battles against Böse the Immortal, \Nthe Seven Sages of Destruction,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.25,0:10:55.01,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,and the Hell Emperor Dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.75,0:10:59.65,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,When I was a kid, I loved \Nthose adventure stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.52,0:11:06.13,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,But the village elders hardly \Never talked about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.20,0:11:10.28,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,They'd talk about how he defeated the monsters
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.28,0:11:12.87,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,that attacked the village, \Nor how he guarded some merchant,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.87,0:11:16.33,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,or even how he just helped \Ncarry stuff like a porter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.60,0:11:21.70,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,They were hardly impressive. \NJust a bunch of boring stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.70,0:11:22.94,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I thought, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.75,0:11:29.39,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,But you could tell how happy the village \Nelders were when they told those stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.68,0:11:35.01,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,After Himmel the Hero died
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.01,0:11:38.51,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,and the remaining demons started \Nacting up, I finally understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.21,0:11:54.72,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,The Thousand-Mirror Tower, Böse, \Nthe Hell Emperor Dragon,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.72,0:11:58.54,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,even the Demon King—none of that \Nhad anything to do with my village.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.63,0:12:03.74,Default,WIREBL,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone had their hands full \Njust maintaining their everyday life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.08,0:12:09.42,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,If Himmel the Hero \Nhadn't come to my village,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.42,0:12:14.62,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,then I doubt it'd still be there, \Nwhether he saved the world or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.87,0:12:17.26,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.58,0:12:23.55,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Those stories of Himmel's less exciting \Nadventures were what guided me here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.51,0:12:28.38,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,That's all I'm trying to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.31,0:12:33.84,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,I've been talking for too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.60,0:12:38.31,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,I'm heading back with those guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.26,0:12:45.03,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, you should treasure \Nthe encounters you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.64,0:12:49.28,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Death isn't the only goodbye in this life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.16,0:12:53.78,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,But I guess you already know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.49,0:13:06.61,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, can't you magic us \Nacross one by one?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.16,0:13:10.38,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'd be left all alone on this side.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.77,0:13:16.01,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Himmel, we need to defeat the \NDemon King as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.01,0:13:19.65,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,What point is there in helping people \Nin these insignificant ways?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.14,0:13:25.56,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,You're right that they're insignificant.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.52,0:13:30.12,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Such deeds won't change the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.10,0:13:36.84,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,But I won't ignore those in need \Nright in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.00,0:13:50.17,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, Himmel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.37,0:13:53.92,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The world has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.51,0:14:02.51,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be granted our privileges tonight, \Nand we're each allowed to bring guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.98,0:14:06.13,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Since we have the opportunity, \Nlet's all go together.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.62,0:14:11.37,DefaultItalics,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,She looks really unhappy about the idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.72,0:14:16.33,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I was told we're allowed to bring guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.02,0:14:22.83,Default,CLERK,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but Ms. Frieren \Nis prohibited per Ms. Serie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.83,0:14:24.43,Default,CLERK,0000,0000,0000,,For the next thousand years,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.43,0:14:27.92,Default,CLERK,0000,0000,0000,,she is barred from entering any \NContinental Magic Association facility.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.59,0:14:31.58,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly did she do to deserve this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.21,0:14:36.87,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be helped. \NI rubbed Serie the wrong way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.39,0:14:41.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,She's like a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.71,0:14:45.14,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not as though \NI wanted to be here anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.14,0:14:46.89,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wait outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.53,0:14:52.37,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wait outside, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.35,0:14:55.78,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.63,0:15:07.39,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That's the early evening bell.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.81,0:15:10.71,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,They should be done receiving \Ntheir privileges soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.71,0:15:11.63,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.09,0:15:14.36,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,A first-class mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.36,0:15:18.25,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The highest level of mage, \Nof whom fewer than fifty exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.91,0:15:21.01,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Fern has grown so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.33,0:15:31.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,In this era, Fern will probably \Nbecome a more famous mage than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.55,0:15:34.69,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.55,0:15:36.81,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.11,0:15:40.25,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.86,0:15:42.43,Default,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.21,0:15:46.43,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.43,0:15:48.87,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,A member of the Continental Magic Association.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.87,0:15:54.71,Default,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the first-class mage Lernen, \None of Ms. Serie's students.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.51,0:15:58.86,Default,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for the trouble \NMs. Serie has caused you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.38,0:16:03.15,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine. She's always been like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.00,0:16:07.90,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Frieren?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.14,0:16:14.10,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You can see the fluctuations \Nin my mana, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.97,0:16:20.74,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're incredibly skilled. \NThis peaceful era doesn't suit you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.74,0:16:27.12,Default,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. I am an old-fashioned mage \Nwho only knows battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.39,0:16:30.01,Default,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Serie often says the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.01,0:16:33.46,Default,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,If I'd been born during the era in which \Nwe fought the Demon King's forces,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.46,0:16:38.67,Default,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,I would've gone down in history \Nalongside the other famous heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.48,0:16:43.14,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So what do you want from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.47,0:16:47.89,Default,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,The only one of Ms. Serie's students \Nwhose name is remembered is her first,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.89,0:16:52.17,Default,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,the Great Mage Flamme \Nspoken of in fairy tales.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.53,0:16:59.14,Default,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,Once I grow old and die, yet another \Nproof of her existence will disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.80,0:17:05.10,Default,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want her to be alone in the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.63,0:17:12.91,Default,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,even if it means going down in infamy \Nas the killer of the legendary mage Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.33,0:17:33.43,Default,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,I request a duel, Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.28,0:17:37.74,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I won't fight you. It'd be a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.51,0:17:39.73,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.41,0:17:45.29,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Mages who only know how to fight \Ncan be so awkward.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.30,0:17:49.12,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need for you to go down in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.46,0:17:53.76,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Serie will remember you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.87,0:17:59.44,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,One last thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.86,0:18:04.38,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,This field of flowers was conjured by magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.47,0:18:07.13,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.84,0:18:10.19,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It was my master's favorite spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.98,0:18:13.90,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you call it useless?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.56,0:18:20.78,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, Flamme was a failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.90,0:18:26.99,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Despite all her talent, \Nshe failed to reach my heights.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.93,0:18:31.72,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I taught many students after her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.55,0:18:36.77,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Most died without ever reaching my level.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.72,0:18:39.79,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,But it's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.45,0:18:43.41,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,They were students I chose on a whim,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.41,0:18:48.29,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,but I can clearly recall each one's \Npersonality and favorite spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.50,0:18:56.65,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, for some reason, I've never \Nregretted taking on any of my students.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.92,0:19:00.59,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Even if they never made their mark on history.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.63,0:19:06.54,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,She can't even tell her own students \Nhow she truly feels.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.35,0:19:09.65,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,She truly is a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.00,0:19:16.08,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.50,0:19:19.76,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I received my privilege.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.76,0:19:21.09,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we go, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.59,0:19:25.09,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, how did you get \Nthat injury on your shoulder?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.47,0:19:28.20,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'd better get it healed at the church.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.20,0:19:29.60,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think they're still open?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.27,0:19:33.61,Default,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,Truly, we are awkward.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.47,0:19:39.20,Default,LERNEN,0000,0000,0000,,Both you and I.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.74,0:19:45.52,Default,BOY,0000,0000,0000,,Stark, what are we gonna do today?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.52,0:19:48.88,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but I can't play today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.88,0:19:51.62,Default,TOWNSFOLK A,0000,0000,0000,,Stark, did you have breakfast this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.62,0:19:53.01,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I already ate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.33,0:19:55.80,Default,TOWNSFOLK B,0000,0000,0000,,Stark, have some of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.80,0:19:57.38,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.01,0:20:01.51,Default,OLD MAN,0000,0000,0000,,The path of the warrior \Nis long and treacherous.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.51,0:20:03.14,Default,OLD MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.99,0:20:04.88,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.48,0:20:11.39,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's time to say goodbye to Äußerst.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.10,0:20:15.55,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,People love you \Neverywhere you go, Mr. Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.55,0:20:16.79,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.42,0:20:21.40,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Fern, what spell \Ndid you end up asking for yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.09,0:20:29.39,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.97,0:20:33.32,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Your clothes are clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.18,0:20:38.07,Default,FREIREN,0000,0000,0000,,And they smell vaguely floral.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.86,0:20:40.42,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.07,0:20:44.41,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a spell to make clothes \Nclean and spotless.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.89,0:20:47.41,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,This will make laundry a breeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.41,0:20:50.43,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Serie the Living Grimoire \Nlived up to her name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.93,0:20:55.18,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's a legendary-level spell \Nfrom the era of mythology.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.58,0:20:58.04,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Well done, Fern.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.87,0:21:02.07,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's my student.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.63,0:21:07.91,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.66,0:21:12.91,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Serie didn't seem at all \Nhappy about it, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.91,0:21:14.83,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Are you insane?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.40,0:21:17.93,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure. Serves her right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.93,0:21:23.33,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,They're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.39,0:21:27.93,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, thank you for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.46,0:21:33.60,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't pass this time, \Nbut we'll try again in three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.60,0:21:35.77,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.27,0:21:37.74,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,It's been fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.74,0:21:38.86,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.13,0:21:40.50,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.50,0:21:42.04,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.95,0:21:58.50,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,That was a rather quick goodbye, \Njust like with Sein.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.50,0:22:00.38,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,And Kraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.67,0:22:15.22,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Himmel, you always say quick goodbyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.70,0:22:16.89,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,You think that's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.25,0:22:20.14,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't seem like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.14,0:22:24.14,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,It was just a side job, but we still \Nspent two weeks traveling together.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.54,0:22:29.34,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,And we drank with him practically every night.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.73,0:22:29.91,FlashbackTop,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You corrupt priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.80,0:22:31.99,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.74,0:22:34.29,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}And you alright
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.65,0:22:36.85,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sure we'll run into each other again \Nif we continue traveling.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.79,0:22:36.79,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Can you hear me
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.58,0:22:43.67,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Trailing along deserted train tracks
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.53,0:22:41.93,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Tearful goodbyes aren't our style.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.67,0:22:45.91,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Crying excessively
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.59,0:22:49.18,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Wanting you to smile
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.90,0:22:50.93,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,After all, it would be embarrassing \Nwhen we met again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.18,0:22:55.22,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}I hold on to memories I'd like to keep fresh
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.22,0:22:58.94,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I'd like to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.94,0:23:01.69,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,With words more precious than a goodbye
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.69,0:23:07.36,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Unremarkable yet special
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.36,0:23:10.91,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,See, things that couldn't have been
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.91,0:23:13.95,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Seen if it weren't for these eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.95,0:23:18.71,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Why? They begin to overflow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.71,0:23:24.71,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So, if I were to be born again
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.71,0:23:30.63,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I would surely choose this place once more
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.63,0:23:36.64,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So, if we were to meet again
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.64,0:23:42.40,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'd never let you go, I'd choose the present
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.40,0:23:45.36,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even if no promises were made
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.36,0:23:48.28,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I'm lost in days of loneliness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.28,0:23:54.45,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Those tears will be alright, \Ndawn will surely break
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.45,0:23:57.12,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'm whispering our lullaby
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.12,0:24:01.04,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,for you to come back home
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.85,0:24:08.60,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It would be embarrassing when we met again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.66,0:24:12.95,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.06,0:24:20.06,Signs_EpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\c&HFAFFF7&\pos(235,269)}Episode 28: It Would Be Embarrassing When We Met Again